The error occurs because set-scaling-config for aws.eks-nodegroup does not support save-options-tag or restore-options-tag, which are specific to ASG/ECS resize actions.

Use mark-for-op in shutdown to tag with original values, then filter and set manually in startup.

This approach captures and restores minSize, desiredSize, maxSize precisely using tags.

Updated Shutdown Policy (Friday)
text
policies:
  - name: eks-nodegroup-shutdown-weekend
    resource: aws.eks-nodegroup
    filters:
      - tag:custodian-weekend-off: true
      - type: value
        key: scalingConfig.minSize
        value: 0
        op: eq
    actions:
      - type: mark-for-op
        tag: CustodianShutdown
        days: 3
        msg: "Saving original scaling: min={{ scalingConfig.minSize }}, desired={{ scalingConfig.desiredSize }}, max={{ scalingConfig.maxSize }}"
      - type: set-scaling-config
        minSize: 0
        desiredSize: 0
        maxSize: present
mark-for-op auto-tags with config values (e.g., CustodianShutdown: Saving original scaling: min=2, desired=3, max=10). Parse later if needed.

Updated Startup Policy (Monday)
text
policies:
  - name: eks-nodegroup-startup-weekdays
    resource: aws.eks-nodegroup
    filters:
      - tag:custodian-weekend-off: true
      - tag:CustodianShutdown: present
    actions:
      - type: set-scaling-config
        minSize: "{{ resources[0].scalingConfig.minSize }}"  # Restore original from saved state or tag parse
        desiredSize: "{{ resources[0].scalingConfig.desiredSize }}"
        maxSize: present
      - type: remove-tag
        tags: ["CustodianShutdown"]
Note: For dynamic restore, parse tag value with JMESPath in filter/action if originals change. Test with --dryrun.

